  <entry>
    <title>Cannot connect Raspberry Pi after a period of time?</title>
    <url>/2022/12/17/Cannot-connect-RespberryPi-after-a-period-of-time/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<img src="https://www.softzone.es/app/uploads-softzone.es/2020/08/Apps-para-Raspberry-Pi.jpg" alt="" style="width:50%" />  

<p>These days, humidifier in the study is working day and night since I wanna reduce formaldehyde content(that’s another story). Around one week later, ghosting appeared on my display screen and finally the root cause turned out to be the humidifier’s water vapor. Moving the monitor to the balcony and under the sunshine, then it works well again.</p>
<p>What drives me crazy is that my Raspberry Pi refused to work almost at the same time! I used to connect my Raspberry Pi via SSH while this time it showed “connection refused”. I was afraid that it was due to the vapor as well and disappointed when it still had no response after one day’s in the sun.</p>
<p>This Saturday, getting time to dig further, I connected the mouse, keyboard and monitor to my lovely Pi, and it’s working! How came I could not SSH to it? It’s the IP address changing!</p>
<p>By default, the Raspberry Pi will get a dynamically allocated IP address, meaning it changes as you restart it or potentially when new devices are added to the network. We could set a static IP address to solve this issue.</p>
<p>[reference] <a href="https://www.ionos.com/digitalguide/server/configuration/provide-raspberry-pi-with-a-static-ip-address/">https://www.ionos.com/digitalguide/server/configuration/provide-raspberry-pi-with-a-static-ip-address/</a></p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center">
<font face='comic'> 
Copyright &copy; 2022-<script>document.write(new Date().getFullYear())</script> Emily Peng All Rights Reserved
</font>
</p>
]]></content>
