    <title>Stringize(#) and token pasting (##) operator in C language</title>
    <url>/2022/11/12/Stringize-and-token-pasting-operator-in-C-language/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<h2 id="Stringizing-operator"><a href="#Stringizing-operator" class="headerlink" title="Stringizing operator"></a>Stringizing operator</h2><p>convert a token to string</p>
<h2 id="Token-passing-operator"><a href="#Token-passing-operator" class="headerlink" title="Token passing operator"></a>Token passing operator</h2><p>Token pasting operator (##) combines or concatenates tokens together.</p>
<p>example:</p>
<figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">#include &lt;stdio.h&gt; </span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">#define PRINT(msg) #msg     // this is used to stringize</span><br><span class="line">#define CONCAT(a, b) a##b   // this is used to concatenate tokens</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">int main()</span><br><span class="line">&#123;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    printf(PRINT(This is a test for stringizing!) &quot;\n&quot;);</span><br><span class="line">    printf(&quot;CONCAT(20, 22) = %d\n&quot;, CONCAT(20, 22));</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    return 0;</span><br><span class="line">&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<p>###Reference:<br>    [1] <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/preprocessor/stringizing-operator-hash?view=msvc-170">https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/preprocessor/stringizing-operator-hash?view=msvc-170</a><br>    [2] <a href="https://codeforwin.org/2018/11/stringize-token-pasting-operator-in-c-language.html">https://codeforwin.org/2018/11/stringize-token-pasting-operator-in-c-language.html</a></p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center">
