    <url>/2022/02/21/6-087-1-Introduction-Writing-compiling-and-debugging-C-programs-Hello-world/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<h1 id="1-What-is-C"><a href="#1-What-is-C" class="headerlink" title="1. What is C?"></a>1. What is C?</h1><h2 id="1-1-widely-used-today"><a href="#1-1-widely-used-today" class="headerlink" title="1.1 widely used today"></a>1.1 widely used today</h2><pre><code>a. extends to newer system architectures
b. efficiency/performance
c. low-level access --&gt; often means faster
</code></pre>
<h2 id="1-2-what-is-C-used-for"><a href="#1-2-what-is-C-used-for" class="headerlink" title="1.2 what is C used for?"></a>1.2 what is C used for?</h2><pre><code>a. OSes, like Linux
b. microcontrollers: automobiles and airplanes
c. embedded processors: phones, portable electronics, etc
d. DSP processors: digital audio and TV systems
</code></pre>
<h2 id="1-3-C-lacks"><a href="#1-3-C-lacks" class="headerlink" title="1.3 C lacks:"></a>1.3 C lacks:</h2><pre><code>a. exceptions
b. range-checking
c. garbage collection
d. object-oriented programming
e. polymorphism
</code></pre>
<h1 id="2-Writing-C-Programs"><a href="#2-Writing-C-Programs" class="headerlink" title="2. Writing C Programs"></a>2. Writing C Programs</h1><h2 id="2-1-steps"><a href="#2-1-steps" class="headerlink" title="2.1 steps"></a>2.1 steps</h2><ol>
<li>edit .c file directly</li>
<li>gcc compiler to get .o file<br><code>gcc -Wall infilename.c -o outfilename.o</code><br>&#x2F;&#x2F; embed debugging info and disable optimization<br><code>gcc -g -o0 -Wall infilename.c -o outfilename.o</code></li>
</ol>
<h1 id="3-Our-First-C-Program"><a href="#3-Our-First-C-Program" class="headerlink" title="3. Our First C Program"></a>3. Our First C Program</h1><h2 id="3-1-structure-of-a-c-file"><a href="#3-1-structure-of-a-c-file" class="headerlink" title="3.1 structure of a .c file"></a>3.1 structure of a .c file</h2><ol>
<li>begin with comments about file contents</li>
<li>insert #include statements and preprocessor definitions</li>
<li>function prototypes and variable declarations</li>
<li>main() function</li>
<li>define other functions</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="3-2-conditional-preprocessor-macros"><a href="#3-2-conditional-preprocessor-macros" class="headerlink" title="3.2 conditional preprocessor macros"></a>3.2 conditional preprocessor macros</h2><p><code>#if, #ifdef, #ifndef, #else, #elif, #endif</code></p>
